  "description": "Non material amendment of condition 10 -\r\rof planning permission 20/AP/0433 (Minor material amendment to planning permission 16/AP/4018 [Approval date: 15.11.2019] 'Redevelopment of the site to provide four buildings to deliver 168 residential dwellings (Class C3) and flexible retail floor space (247m2) of flexible A1/A3/A4; The works include the conversion and extension of Sumner House (Block A) from office use (Class B1-c to provide 44 no flats and 4 no townhouses and partial\rdemolition of boundary wall; the erection of a part 4, part 6 storey block to provide 39 no flats on Sumner Avenue (Block B); part 4(Block B); a part four, part 6 storey building to provide 72 no flats on Jocelyn Street (Block C); and a four storey block providing 9 flats on Melon Road (Block D), with 247m2 of flexible A1/A3/A4 use at ground floor level together with car parking, hard and soft landscaping, and other associated works incidental to the development' consisting of: \r- One change to the design of Flaxyard Block B:\r- Switching the balcony/terrace balustrades from glass to solid panels;\r- Changes to the design of Flaxyard Block C, including:\r- Enlargement of building footprint on floors 04 to 05;\r- Small number of fenestration changes;\r- Reduction in size of the external cycle store, but with a separate supplementary store to now be provided;\r- Changes to the design of Flaxyard Block D, including:\r- Enlargement of building footprint on floors 01 to 03;\r- Reduction of floorspace of the commercial unit from 247m2 to 224.5m2;\r- External door changes;\r- Changes to landscaping and car parking arrangements.) to amend the wording of condition 10 to allow the condition to be partially  discharged to comply with Blocks B, C and D.\r",
